o/BV1Rq4y197u8?spm_id_from=333.788.top_right_bar_window_history.content.click#t=325.58872","line":10},{"title":"05:53","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?spm_id_from=333.788.top_right_bar_window_history.content.click#t=353.610321","line":12},{"title":"09:06","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?spm_id_from=333.788.top_right_bar_window_history.content.click#t=546.676935","line":16},{"title":"13:51","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=3#t=831.320189","line":24},{"title":"DDD（领域驱动设计）-讲给P8听的业务设计课！理论+实践（坦克大战/抽丝剥茧设计模式），一个案例透彻理解！_哔哩哔哩_bilibili","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=3","line":31},{"title":"12:36","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=3#t=756.563503","line":35},{"title":"18:02","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=3#t=1082.92385","line":39},{"title":"35:00","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=3#t=2100.268763","line":52},{"title":"40:38","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=3#t=2438.450583","line":54},{"title":"DDD（领域驱动设计）-讲给P8听的业务设计课！理论+实践（坦克大战/抽丝剥茧设计模式），一个案例透彻理解！_哔哩哔哩_bilibili","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=4","line":57},{"title":"31:54","target":"https://www.bilibili.com/video/BV1Rq4y197u8?p=4#t=1914.161987","line":60},{"title":"地图就是模型，而模型被用来描绘人们所关注的现实或想法的某个方面。模型是一种简化。它是对现实的解释一一把与解决问题密切相关的方面抽象出来，而忽略无关的细节。","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/%E9%A2%86%E5%9F%9F%E9%A9%B1%E5%8A%A8%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%20%E8%BD%AF%E4%BB%B6%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E5%A4%8D%E6%9D%82%E6%80%A7%E5%BA%94%E5%AF%B9%E4%B9%8B%E9%81%93%20%E4%BF%AE%E8%AE%A2%E7%89%88%20by%20%EF%BC%88%E7%BE%8E%EF%BC%89EricEvans%E8%91%97%20(z-lib.org","line":72},{"title":"每个软件程序是为了执行用户的某项活动，或是满足用户的某种需求。这些用户应用软件的问题区域就是软件的领域。","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/%E9%A2%86%E5%9F%9F%E9%A9%B1%E5%8A%A8%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%20%E8%BD%AF%E4%BB%B6%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E5%A4%8D%E6%9D%82%E6%80%A7%E5%BA%94%E5%AF%B9%E4%B9%8B%E9%81%93%20%E4%BF%AE%E8%AE%A2%E7%89%88%20by%20%EF%BC%88%E7%BE%8E%EF%BC%89EricEvans%E8%91%97%20(z-lib.org","line":74},{"title":"The design of the old application, if there was one, had accreted as one capability after another had been laid on top of the existing code, without any noticeable generalization or abstraction.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":79},{"title":"从句详解#^1d0e32","target":"从句详解#^1d0e32","line":81},{"title":"But the second time around, if the developers perceive analysis to be a separate process, modeling happens in a less disciplined way.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":85},{"title":"701","target":"booknote/books-data/resources/(annots)领域驱动设计 软件核心复杂性应对之道 修订版 by （美）EricEvans著 (z-lib.org).pdf/p57r13.530,246.200,434.400,558.350z2i(cd683868-0233-3118-fb4c-558f62a15f68).png#center","line":88},{"title":"如果编写代码的人员认为自己没必要对模型负责，或者不知道如何让模型为应用程序服务，那么这个模型就和程序没有任何关联。如果开发人员没有意识到改变代码就意昧着改变模型，那么他们对程序的重构不但不会增强模型的作用，反而还会削弱它的效果。同样，如果建模人员不参与到程序实现的过程中，那么对程序实现的约束就没有切身的感受，即使有，也会很快忘记。MODEL-DRIVEN DESIGN的两个基本要素（即模型要支持有效的实现并抽象出关键的领域知识）已经失去了一个，最终模型将变得不再实用。最后一点，如果分工阻断了设计人员与开发人员之间的协作，使他们无法转达实现MODEL-DRIVEN DESIGN的种种细节，那么经验丰富的设计人员则不能将自己的知识和技术传递给开发人员。","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/%E9%A2%86%E5%9F%9F%E9%A9%B1%E5%8A%A8%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%20%E8%BD%AF%E4%BB%B6%E6%A0%B8%E5%BF%83%E5%A4%8D%E6%9D%82%E6%80%A7%E5%BA%94%E5%AF%B9%E4%B9%8B%E9%81%93%20%E4%BF%AE%E8%AE%A2%E7%89%88%20by%20%EF%BC%88%E7%BE%8E%EF%BC%89EricEvans%E8%91%97%20(z-lib.org","line":91},{"title":"The domain model is a set of concepts. The “domain layer” is the manifestation of that model and all directly related design elements. The design and implementation of business logic constitute the domain layer. In a MODEL-DRIVEN DESIGN, the software constructs of the domain layer mirror the model concepts.","target":"obsidian://booknote?type=annotation&book=resources/Domain-Driven%20Design%20Tackling%20Complexity%20in%20the%20Heart%20of%20Software%20by%20Eric%20Evans%20(z-lib.org","line":93},{"title":"DDD 的基本要素（第五章）","target":"DDD 的基本要素（第五章）","line":99},{"title":"DDD 的基本要素（第六章）","target":"DDD 的基本要素（第六章）","line":100},{"title":"DDD 的实战 （第七章）","target":"DDD 的实战 （第七章）","line":101}],"blocks":{"#":[1,5],"#MVC vs DDD":[6,102],"#MVC vs DDD#{1}":[8,94],"#MVC vs DDD#{2}":[95,95],"#MVC vs DDD#{3}":[96,96],"#MVC vs DDD#{4}":[97,97],"#MVC vs DDD#{5}":[98,98],"#MVC vs DDD#{6}":[99,102]},"last_import":{"mtime":1655030456067,"size":8692,"at":0,"hash":"bfb8484fa1c80c0922bbb23637f10a5615c8d79ae4cd4f5f120f3bc4faa80288"},"key":"DDD 记录.md"},
